<paragraph blockId="7.[151,610,438,464]" box="[151,610,438,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="527">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,610,438,464]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="7" pageNumber="527" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Westwood, 1834" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1834" box="[151,610,438,464]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,610,438,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="527">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,400,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="527">Microvelia pulchella</emphasis>
Westwood, 1834
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,509,714]" pageId="7" pageNumber="527">
This is one of the most widely distributed species of the genus, with records from 
<collectingCountry box="[1109,1193,509,534]" name="Canada" pageId="7" pageNumber="527">Canada</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[1234,1346,509,534]" name="Argentina" pageId="7" pageNumber="527">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(Pérez- 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,450,545,570]" pageId="7" pageNumber="527" refId="ref6294" refString="Perez-Gelabert, D. E. &amp; Floriano, C. F. B. (2016) New records of the water strider Platyvelia brachialis (Stal 1860) (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Veliidae) from the Dominican Republic and Haiti, with a checklist of the West Indian Veliidae. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 118, 471 - 476. https: // doi. org / 10.4289 / 0013 - 8797.118.3.471" type="journal article">Gelabert &amp; Floriano 2016</bibRefCitation>
), and is commonly collected together with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uhler" authorityYear="1894" box="[945,1079,545,569]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis box="[945,1079,545,569]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="527">M. longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="White" authorityYear="1879" box="[1137,1260,545,569]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">
<emphasis box="[1137,1260,545,569]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="527">M. mimula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in small pools. We present here the first record from 
<collectingRegion box="[571,739,581,606]" country="France" name="Guyane" pageId="7" pageNumber="527">
<collectingCountry box="[571,739,581,606]" name="French Guiana" pageId="7" pageNumber="527">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
, where the three species co-occur.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
